Heat oil in a large, heavy nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add bell pepper and onion and stir-fry for 3-4 minutes. Add sausage and stir-fry for 2 minutes. Add zucchini, mushrooms, Italian seasoning and 1/4 tsp black pepper. Stir-fry only until crisp. Remove from heat, add vinegar and toss to coat all ingredients. Meanwhile, microwave polenta rounds in covered container for 1 to 2 minutes or until hot throughout. Portion 2 to 3 polenta rounds on each plate and top with sauteed vegetables.